{
  "texts": [
    "To reassure users, some tech companies choose not to use user input data for training AI models, thereby avoiding potential privacy risks.",
    "This method typically relies on pre-prepared, depersonalized datasets or simulated data.",
    "The downside is that it may limit the learning effectiveness and application scope of the AI model, as the model cannot learn and iterate from real-time user feedback.",
    "In the U.S., some tech companies prohibit employees from uploading company-related information to large models like ChatGPT.",
    "For example, Microsoft implemented a new policy banning its employees from using ChatGPT or any other third-party chatbots for work-related purposes."
  ]
}